news.title: BMC delays uploading of documents for auction of three plots in Mumbai
news.para: Uploading of tender documents regarding its proposed auction of three of its plots in prime areas of the city, namely Malabar Hill, Worli, and Crawford Market

news.title: Akzo Nobel open for partnership or sell off its Indian operations: CEO
news.para: Earlier this month, Akzo Nobel had said that it would be conducting a strategic review of its decorative paints business in South Asia.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to launch online trading platform for development rights certificates
news.para: Individual societies or flat owners will now be able to purchase small amounts of DRC for regularisation or extension purposes without relying on brokers.

news.title: NGT orders Haryana SEIAA to investigate illegal construction at Mayfield Garden
news.para: NGT, while hearing the case in April earlier this year, had passed an interim order directing Haryana State Pollution Control Board (HSPCB) to ensure that illegal construction was not carried out in Mayfield Garden.

news.title: Flats registration begin at Noida’s Lotus 300 after SC order
news.para: The Supreme Court on Sept 27 upheld an order by the Allahabad high court and directed the Noida Authority to proceed with registries at the Sector 107 society regardless of pending land dues by the developer.

news.title: Applicants filed petition in Karnataka HC over 12 year delay in EWS housing project
news.para: As per the plan, the builder has to construct 1,512 residential quarters in 26 blocks with nine-storeyed structures with lift facilities in an area of 7.2 acres. However, 12 years since construction began, work is far from over.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA mandates broker fee disclosure in property sale agreements
news.para: The issuing of the order by MahaRERA helps in recognising the fact that real estate agents are entitled to brokerage in transactions enabled by the agent, pointed out a real estate agent.

news.title: Macrotech Developers posts net profit of Rs 423.10 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Macrotech Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,684.60 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 52.96 per cent from Rs 1,755.10 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills' net profit declines 4.34% in Q2 FY25
news.para: The Phoenix Mills' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 955.06 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 5.34 per cent from Rs 906.64 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' loss narrows to Rs 13.99 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 15.96 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 37.90 per cent from Rs 25.70 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Spain's Malaga to ban new holiday flat permits in 43 neighbourhoods
news.para: Malaga joins other cities in cracking down on short-term rentals, including Barcelona, which plans to scrap licences for tourist rentals by 2028.

news.title: DLF posts net profit of Rs 1,381.22 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: DLF's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,180.83 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 47.71 per cent from Rs 1,476.42 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sales of new homes in USA up 6.3% year-on-year in September 2024
news.para: Sales of new homes in the United States last month exceeded analyst expectations Thursday, logging the fastest pace in more than a year on the back of cooler mortgage rates. The rate was higher than a consensus of analysts expected.

news.title: Wells Fargo may lose up to $3 billion on its office building loans
news.para: Earlier this month, Chief Financial Officer Michael Santomassimo had warned investors in a post-earnings call that the bank expects losses in the office loan portfolio to be lumpy.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net profit declines by 10.31% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Mindspace REIT clocked net operating income (NOI) of Rs 504 crore, registersing a growth of 5.1% year-on-year in Q2 FY25. The board of directors of K Raheja Corp Investment Managers, manager to Mindspace REIT declared distribution of Rs 5.15 per unit aggregating to Rs 305.40 crore

news.title: Orient Electric's net profit dips 43.41% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Orient Electric's net total income stood at Rs 664.34 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 16.50 per cent from Rs 570.26 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Arvind Smartspaces posts net profit of Rs 42.60 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Arvind Smartspaces' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 269.28 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 257.75 per cent from Rs 75.27 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Urban Vault leases 1.2 lakh sq ft office spaces in Bengaluru
news.para: Amal Mishra, founder of Urban Vault said, "We are expanding in Gurugram in the next quarter. Pune and Mumbai are also in the expansion plans."

news.title: Flipspaces eyes Rs 320 crore revenue in FY25
news.para: Flipspaces claims to be nearing Rs 400 crore revenue run rate and is looking for further expansion through acquisitions in India and the US.

news.title: Chhattisgarh government launches 'Sugam App' for online property registration
news.para: ​The application, called 'Sugam (convenient) App', was launched on October 21 with an aim to make the property registration process more transparent and user-friendly, the public relations department official said.
